
[1]truce

   TRUCE, n.

   1. In war, a suspension of arms by agreement of the commanders; a
   temporary cessation of hostilities, either for negotiation or other
   purpose.

   2. Intermission of action, pain or contest; temporary cessation; short
   quiet.

   There he may find

   Truce to his restless thoughts.
